for president have called for
greater action.

14:03.509 --> 14:09.282 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Secretary Clinton, who
certainly understands
what's happening in Asia, has
called for greater

14:09.315 --> 14:14.253 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
sanctions and to ensure, as I
think we all
feel, that we not allow North
Korea to blackmail

14:14.287 --> 14:19.559 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the international community, but
that we take
resolute action to tell them,
this is not

14:19.592 --> 14:21.360 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
acceptable.

14:21.394 --> 14:24.297 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Siegfried Hecker,
let's talk about
resolute action for a moment. A
year ago,

14:24.330 --> 14:28.901 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
