were getting
out of control and he wasn't
being seen as

16:42.702 --> 16:44.570 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
primary.

16:44.604 --> 16:48.040 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So this was a way to bring his
country together,
which we find completely
reprehensible, but,

16:48.074 --> 16:52.211 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
nonetheless, he's taken that
action. Second,
he's sending a message to the
region and to

16:52.245 --> 16:57.516 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the United States that he will
do whatever
he thinks he needs to do to
protect his country.

16:57.550 --> 17:00.887 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He will not go down, as other
leaders have
gone down around the world.

17:00.920 --> 17:07.226 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I take Sieg's statements, and I
understand
them, the frustration here to
get North Korea

17:07.260 --> 17:11.063 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to do something, but to get
action takes a
couple of things. It takes a
leader who is

17:11.097 --> 17:14.901 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
willing to engage. And North
Korea has not
been willing to engage, though
the United

17:14.934 --> 17:18.704 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
States and others have made many
entreaties
to them to do so.

17:18.738 --> 17:24.844 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, secondly, I think we have
to get China,
who has really one of the only
relationships

17:24.877 --> 17:30.716 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
left with North Korea, along
perhaps a little
bit with Russia, to not only
engage, but also

17:30.750 --> 17:35.922 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to take tougher action to take
away some of
the goodies that they still
provide to North

17:35.955 --> 17:37.757 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Korea.

17:37.790 --> 17:39.859 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: And, finally,
