beyond my
own personal reach.

17:51.470 --> 17:58.244 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the thing that seems clear,
just in terms
of the nuclear weapons piece of
this, is that

17:58.277 --> 18:03.516 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
North Korea looks at these
nuclear weapons
as a deterrent. During all of my
visits and

18:03.549 --> 18:08.521 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the discussions with their
Foreign Ministry
and the diplomats, rather than
the technical

18:08.554 --> 18:10.990 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
people, they talked about their
deterrent.

18:11.023 --> 18:17.730 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So the emphasis was always
deterrent, meaning
deterring the United States from
essentially,

18:17.763 --> 18:25.571 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
you know, going into North
Korea, or, as they
like to say, you know, our
hostile policies.

18:25.604 --> 18:32.845 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, I think we need to
understand exactly
what is the North Korean
security concern,

18:32.878 --> 18:37.450 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
because without getting over
that concern,
in North Korea, to come to
resolution, it

18:37.483 --> 18:41.854 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
seems to me -- and, again, not
being a diplomat
-- that the issue is much bigger
than just

18:41.887 --> 18:47.860 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the nuclear issue. And so
focusing on the
nuclear issue by itself is not
going to be

18:47.893 --> 18:49.795 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
able to get us there.

18:49.829 --> 18:54.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Siegfried Hecker,
former director
of the Los Alamos Laboratory,
and Wendy Sherman,

18:54.133 --> 18:59.572 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
